odal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 13, 2022</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104vhi1665702962331.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/vhi1665702962331.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/vhi1665702962331.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"vhi1665702962331\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n       Data Packing for SEQ Connector\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"vhi1665702962331__data_packing_for_seq_connector_171375\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">There are no field data types or packing codes in the same way as for a field-level DBMS—data is simply stored as entered.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vhi1665702962331__p_d58319e1_d58320e1_d58321e1\">The connector creates and accesses sequential files only. It does not manage fields. When you create a table at run time, the connector creates a file to which everything is sequentially added. The connector handles the data in the file according to the conceptual definitions which you have already created. Records are stored in the same way as they are handled internally within Uniface.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"vhi1665702962331__topic_d38597e1_d38598e1_d38599e1_d38600e1_d38601e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d724372e56\">\n                        \n Default Storage Format for Certain Fields\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"vhi1665702962331__p_d58325e1_d58326e1_d58327e1\">Some combinations of data type and packing code cause the SEQ connector to store data in a certain way. The table shows how Uniface packing codes are stored by the connector:</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"vhi1665702962331__table_d5309e1_d5310e1_d5311e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Storage of Uniface Packing Codes by Sequential File Connectors</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"vhi1665702962331__table_d5309e1_d5310e1_d5311e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Uniface</p>\n</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"vhi1665702962331__table_d5309e1_d5310e1_d5311e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Sequential files</p>\n</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vhi1665702962331__table_d5309e1_d5310e1_d5311e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">D</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vhi1665702962331__table_d5309e1_d5310e1_d5311e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">D3 ASCII date DDMMYYYY</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vhi1665702962331__table_d5309e1_d5310e1_d5311e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">E</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vhi1665702962331__table_d5309e1_d5310e1_d5311e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">E4 ASCII datetime DDMMYYYY HHNNSS</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vhi1665702962331__table_d5309e1_d5310e1_d5311e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">F</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vhi1665702962331__table_d5309e1_d5310e1_d5311e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">C20</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vhi1665702962331__table_d5309e1_d5310e1_d5311e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">T</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"vhi1665702962331__table_d5309e1_d5310e1_d5311e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">T1 ASCII time HH:NN:SS</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533021\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533021\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Data Packing for SEQ Connector Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 13, 2022 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Data Packing for SEQ Connector There are no field data types or packing codes in the same way as for a field-level DBMS—data is simply stored as entered. The connector creates and accesses sequential files only. It does not manage fields. When you create a table at run time, the connector creates a file to which everything is sequentially added. The connector handles the data in the file according to the conceptual definitions which you have already created. Records are stored in the same way as they are handled internally within Uniface. Default Storage Format for Certain Fields Some combinations of data type and packing code cause the SEQ connector to store data in a certain way. The table shows how Uniface packing codes are stored by the connector: Table 1. Storage of Uniface Packing Codes by Sequential File Connectors Uniface Sequential files D D3 ASCII date DDMMYYYY E E4 ASCII datetime DDMMYYYY HHNNSS F C20 T T1 ASCII time HH:NN:SS Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}